    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Michael Manlich (Bratislava, 15 February
                    1550)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">The late Pál Várday owed doctor Joannes Maria Cataneus
                            111 florins and 50 denarii, which debt Oláh has assumed. He asks that he
                            pay 75 florins from the above-mentioned sum, which he will settle, and
                            he should keep the receipt (which either the physician or a
                            representative of his will provide to him).</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Carissime Domine Manli!<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Michael
                        Manlich was a factor of the Fuggers in Vienna, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Laczlavik</hi> 2014, 121. On the network of the Manlich family, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Tózsa-Rigó</hi> 2013, 31.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Debebat reverendissimus quondam dominus
                        <persName>Paulus</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Pál Várday
                        died on 12 October, 1549.</note> archiepiscopus Strigoniensis huic domino
                        <persName>Ioanni Mariae Cataneo</persName>,<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">Johannes Maria Cataneus. We know a physician with the same
                        name from the 1510s, who was in the service of Emperor Maximilian I, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kostenzer</hi> 1970, 79–80. It is not clear if this is
                        the same physician.</note> artis medicae doctori, centum et undecem Florenos
                    Hungaricos in monetis et denarios quinquaginta, quos nos in nos ipsos
                    recepimus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Quare rogamus vos, velitis nomine nostro ipsi domino
                        <persName>Ioanni Mariae</persName> doctori, vel homini suo, hos centum et
                    undecem Florenos et quinquaginta denarios, singularem Florenum per septuaginta
                    quinque cruciferos computandos persolvere, quos nos apud vos rectificabimus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Praesentes vero una cum litteris quietantiae<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">A letter of discharge from debt.</note> praefati
                        <persName>Ioannis Mariae</persName> doctoris, vel hominis sui, qui plenum
                    mandatum ab eo habuerit, pro vestra expeditione reservare.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Datum <placeName>Posonii</placeName> quindecima die Februarii anno
                    Domini millesimo quingentisemo quinquagesimo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">
                    <seg type="signature">Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Agriensis, cancellarius regiae
                        maiestatis etc. manu propria</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Domino Michaeli Manli factori Fucarorum Viennae constituto etc.
                    amico nobis honorando.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
